### 4. Rigorous Component-by-Component Comparison (Origin vs Sean)

#### 4.1 Poseidon

| | Ours | Sean's |
|---|---|---|
| **Widths** | T=3, T=4, T=6 | T=3, T=6 only (no T=4) |
| **T=3 algorithm** | Sparse-matrix optimization (Filecoin/Neptune) -- saves ~228 mulmod ops | Dense MDS multiply every round |
| **const fn** | None | All functions are `const fn` |
| **Compile-time verification** | None -- runtime tests only | 4 `static_assert`s verify hashes at compile time |
| **Constants storage** | Flat arrays in separate files (1167 lines) | Cascading `if round == N` branches returning tuples (1369 lines) |
| **Field arithmetic** | Inline `addmod(x, y, PRIME)` | Wrapped in `const fn field_add/field_mul` -- cleaner, impossible to pass wrong modulus |
| **Tests** | 8 runtime tests (T=4 gas limits prevented testing hash5 with nonzero inputs) | 0 runtime tests, but 4 `static_assert`s (no gas limit issues) |
| **Auditability** | Sparse constants require trust in circomlibjs optimization pipeline | Raw unoptimized constants, more directly auditable |

Both produce identical outputs for identical inputs. Same BN254 field, same x^5 S-box, same round counts (65 for T=3, 68 for T=6). The sparse-matrix optimization in ours saves ~1,824 gas for T=3 partial rounds.

**Ideal merge:** Our sparse-matrix T=3 optimization + our T=4 support + Sean's `const fn` + `static_assert`.

#### 4.2 Binary IMT

| | Ours (`imt` + `binary_merkle_root`) | Sean's (`binary_imt`) |
|---|---|---|
| **Operations** | Verify + compute_root only | Full CRUD: init, insert, update, remove, verify |
| **State** | Stateless free functions | Stateful `BinaryIMTData` struct tracking subtrees, zero hashes, leaf count |
| **Depth handling** | Const generics `<const DEPTH: usize>` | Runtime `MAX_DEPTH=32` with bounds checking |
| **Proof format** | `path_index: u256` bitfield (compact) + `[u256; N]` array variant | `[u8; 32]` indices (32 bytes vs our 1024 bytes for array variant) |
| **Error handling** | None -- returns bare `bool` | 8-variant `IMTError` enum, validates all inputs |
| **Tests** | 12 tests, hand-computed vectors | 28 tests including hardcoded hex roots matching Solidity |
| **Completeness vs Solidity** | ~15-20% | ~95% |

Sean's is a near-complete port of `BinaryIMT.sol`. Ours covers only verification (~15-20% of the surface).

